description: Updates an OpenSearch Serverless-managed interface endpoint. For more information, see Access Amazon OpenSearch Serverless using an interface endpoint.

parameters.name: id
parameters.description: The unique identifier of the interface endpoint to update.

parameters.name: addSubnetIds
parameters.description: The ID of one or more subnets to add to the endpoint. (string) ---

parameters.name: removeSubnetIds
parameters.description: The unique identifiers of the subnets to remove from the endpoint. (string) ---

parameters.name: addSecurityGroupIds
parameters.description: The unique identifiers of the security groups to add to the endpoint. Security groups define the ports, protocols, and sources for inbound traffic that you are authorizing into your endpoint. (string) ---

parameters.name: removeSecurityGroupIds
parameters.description: The unique identifiers of the security groups to remove from the endpoint. (string) ---

parameters.name: clientToken
parameters.description: Unique, case-sensitive identifier to ensure idempotency of the request. This field is autopopulated if not provided.

nested_items.name: UpdateVpcEndpointDetail
nested_items.description: Details about the updated VPC endpoint.

nested_items.name: id
nested_items.description: The unique identifier of the endpoint.

nested_items.name: status
nested_items.description: The current status of the endpoint update process.

nested_items.name: subnetIds
nested_items.description: The ID of the subnets from which you access OpenSearch Serverless.

nested_items.name: securityGroupIds
nested_items.description: The unique identifiers of the security groups that define the ports, protocols, and sources for inbound traffic that you are authorizing into your endpoint.

nested_items.name: lastModifiedDate
nested_items.description: The timestamp of when the endpoint was last modified.
